Vol / Page:  251
Edition:
Quote:  Maori name for Red Ochre, an oxide of iron deposited in certain rivers, used by the Maoris for painting. it was usually mixed with shark oil, but for very fine work with oil from the berries of the <i>titoki</i>(q.v.).
